cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on wireless communication technologies and their suitability for CAV applications. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as CAVs are often associated with AI and machine learning. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as CAVs involve control systems and automation. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the information and data transmission aspects of wireless communication technologies. 
- cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as security and privacy are important considerations in CAVs and their communication systems.
